> How does 35+ years age affect the load carrying capacity of a Bus?  I
hauled about 1/2 cubuic yard of topsoil, which I estimated at about
1300-1400 lbs (very rough numbers: 1/2 of 27 cu ft at around 100 lb/cu ft).
I had all the seats out and my Bus is a '68 7-passenger model.  My Bus
looked like it was sitting about 3-4 inches lower than empty, and it
certainly drove like it was quite heavy, but it was not bottoming out or
having any other driveability issues.  From my research, the original rating
of the vehicle was about 2000 lbs useful load, so I felt reasonably safe
that I didn't overload it.  Does anyone out there have more information on
how the suspension (I'm pretty sure mine is the original; front beam has no
major rust or other problems I can detect) deteriorates over time and maybe
some guesses at safe limits as time passes?
